category.name: PrisonersByState
category.description: This datasets describes the number of prisoners under Jurisdiction of Federal or State Correctional Authorities by state in 1990, 2000, 2005, and 2006. A year ending is December 31. To have jurisdiction over a prisoner, a state or the federal system must have legal authority over the prisoner. FOOTNOTES: 1 U.S. total includes federal prisoners not distributed by state and prison system. 2 Data includes both total jail and prison population.
